comments.body:
Hi, the problem is that you're calling `uppy.on()` at the top level of your component. This means that it is run every time your component rerenders, adding an additional listener each time.

Instead, you can use React's builtin `useEffect()` hook to replace the event listener whenever you receive a different `handleFileUploaded` function‚Äîthis way you will only have one at a time.

```js
useEffect(() => {
  const handler = (status, event) => {
    props.handleFileUploaded(event.body);
  };
  uppy.on('upload-success', handler);
  // Tell React to remove the old listener if a different function is passed to the `handleFileUploaded` prop:
  return () => {
    uppy.off('upload-success', handler);
  };
}, [props.handleFileUploaded]);
```

