The progress bar shows progress for the entire upload, not individual files. Eg if one out of 4 files completed but the other 3 are stuck at 0%, the progress bar will show 25%.

You could write a custom UI that does this by listening for the `upload-start`, `upload-progress` events:

```js
uppy.on('upload-start', (fileID) => {
  const file = uppy.getFile(fileID)
  addProgressBar(file)
})
uppy.on('upload-progress', (data) => {
  const file = uppy.getFile(data.id)
  updateProgressBar(file, data)
})
uppy.on('file-removed', (file) => {
  removeProgressBar(file)
})

function addProgressBar (file) {
  // append a custom progress bar with label `file.name`
}
function updateProgressBar (file, progress) {
  // set progress bar values based on progress.bytesTotal and progress.bytesUploaded
}
```

(Note that the `upload-start` and `upload-progress` event APIs are being changed in #647, so you would need to update the snippet in the future‚Äîthe changes are small though!)

